The paper deals with optimizing the beamforming protocol for an intelligent reflecting surface (IRS) in a wireless communication system. This involves statistical channel state information (S-CSI) and instantaneous channel state information (I-CSI), which are relevant to information theory (cs.IT), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), control systems (cs.SY), multimedia (cs.MM), and computational linguistics (cs.CL). However, since the paper focuses more on the technical aspects of wireless communication and optimization, cs.IT and cs.NI are the most likely categories, followed by cs.SY, cs.MM, and cs.CL.
